## 6. Section Cards

### 6.1 Hero Section (001 ‚Äî Overview)

**Card:** `HeroSection extends SectionCard`

**Fields:**
- `eyebrow: StringField` ‚Äî "001 ‚Äî Overview"
- `headlineWord1: StringField` ‚Äî "Compose" (gets gradient)
- `headlineWord2: StringField` ‚Äî "Everything."
- `tagline: StringField` ‚Äî "Build what you use. Use what you build."
- `description: StringField` ‚Äî Full paragraph
- `primaryCtaText: StringField` ‚Äî "Start Building"
- `primaryCtaUrl: UrlField`
- `secondaryCtaText: StringField` ‚Äî "Read the Vision ‚Üí"
- `secondaryCtaUrl: UrlField`
- `badges: containsMany(BadgeField)` ‚Äî Open source strip items
- `backgroundGrid: linksTo(() => AnimatedGrid)` ‚Äî Animated card background

**BadgeField (FieldDef):**
- `icon: StringField` ‚Äî GitHub icon SVG or emoji
- `label: StringField` ‚Äî "100% Open Source"
- `url: UrlField` ‚Äî Optional link

**Template Features:**
- Composited `AnimatedGrid` card as background layer
- Gradient text on highlight word
- Frosted glass effect on text container
- Open source badge strip

**Composition Pattern:**
The hero section uses the AnimatedGrid card as a background layer:

```gts
static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
  <template>
    <section class="hero-section">
      {{! Background layer - composited card }}
      {{#if @model.backgroundGrid}}
        <div class="background-layer">
          <@fields.backgroundGrid @format="isolated" />
        </div>
      {{/if}}

      {{! Content layer }}
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="hero-eyebrow">{{@model.eyebrow}}</div>
        <h1 class="hero-headline">
          <span class="word-1">{{@model.headlineWord1}}</span>
          <span class="word-2">{{@model.headlineWord2}}</span>
        </h1>
        <!-- Rest of hero content -->
      </div>
    </section>

    <style scoped>
      .hero-section {
        position: relative;
        padding-block: var(--hero-padding-block, var(--section-padding-block));
        padding-inline: var(--section-padding-inline);
        overflow: hidden;
      }

      .background-layer {
        position: absolute;
        inset: 0;
        z-index: 0;
        opacity: 0.6; /* Subtle background effect */
      }

      .hero-content {
        position: relative;
        z-index: 1;
        max-width: var(--section-max-width);
        margin-inline: auto;
      }
    </style>
  </template>
};
```

---

### 6.2 Animated Grid Card

**Card:** `AnimatedGrid extends CardDef`

**Purpose:** Reusable animated card grid background that can be composited into sections.

**Fields:**
- `gridColumns: NumberField` ‚Äî Number of columns (default: 6)
- `gridRows: NumberField` ‚Äî Number of rows (default: 4)
- `animationSpeed: StringField` ‚Äî "slow" | "medium" | "fast"
- `cardOpacity: NumberField` ‚Äî 0.0 to 1.0 (default: 0.3)
- `accentColor: StringField` ‚Äî Hex color for highlight cards

**Template Features:**
- CSS Grid layout with specified columns/rows
- Randomly highlighted cards with accent color
- Subtle animation using CSS animations
- Fully self-contained with scoped styles

**Usage:**
This card is designed to be composited into other sections as a background layer:

```gts
// In hero-section.gts
export class HeroSection extends SectionCard {
  @field backgroundGrid = linksTo(() => AnimatedGrid);

  static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
    <template>
      <section class="hero-section">
        {{#if @model.backgroundGrid}}
          <div class="background-layer">
            <@fields.backgroundGrid @format="isolated" />
          </div>
        {{/if}
        <div class="hero-content">
          <!-- Hero content here -->
        </div>
      </section>
    </template>
  };
}
```

**AnimatedGrid Template:**

```gts
export class AnimatedGrid extends CardDef {
  static displayName = 'Animated Grid';

  @field gridColumns = contains(NumberField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 6; }
  });

  @field gridRows = contains(NumberField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 4; }
  });

  @field animationSpeed = contains(StringField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 'medium'; }
  });

  @field cardOpacity = contains(NumberField, {
    computeVia: function() { return 0.3; }
  });

  @field accentColor = contains(StringField, {
    computeVia: function() { return '#00ffba'; }
  });

  static isolated = class Isolated extends Component<typeof this> {
    get totalCells() {
      return (this.args.model?.gridColumns ?? 6) * (this.args.model?.gridRows ?? 4);
    }

    get cellArray() {
      return Array.from({ length: this.totalCells }, (_, i) => i);
    }

    <template>
      <div class="animated-grid" style="
        --grid-columns: {{@model.gridColumns}};
        --grid-rows: {{@model.gridRows}};
        --card-opacity: {{@model.cardOpacity}};
        --accent-color: {{@model.accentColor}};
      ">
        {{#each this.cellArray as |index|}}
          <div class="grid-cell" data-index={{index}}></div>
        {{/each}}
      </div>

      <style scoped>
        .animated-grid {
          width: 100%;
          height: 100%;
          display: grid;
          grid-template-columns: repeat(var(--grid-columns, 6), 1fr);
          grid-template-rows: repeat(var(--grid-rows, 4), 1fr);
          gap: 1rem;
          padding: 2rem;
        }

        .grid-cell {
          background: rgba(255, 255, 255, var(--card-opacity, 0.3));
          border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
          border-radius: var(--radius, 0.5rem);
          transition: all 0.3s ease;
        }

        /* Highlight random cells with accent color */
        .grid-cell:nth-child(3),
        .grid-cell:nth-child(7),
        .grid-cell:nth-child(12),
        .grid-cell:nth-child(19) {
          background: var(--accent-color);
          box-shadow: 0 0 2rem var(--accent-color);
        }

        /* Subtle animation */
        @keyframes pulse {
          0%, 100% { opacity: 1; }
          50% { opacity: 0.6; }
        }

        .grid-cell {
          animation: pulse 3s ease-in-out infinite;
          animation-delay: calc(var(--grid-columns) * 0.1s * random());
        }
      </style>
    </template>
  };
}
```

**Instance Example:**

```json
// examples/AnimatedGrid/hero-background.json
{
  "data": {
    "type": "card",
    "id": "https://realms.../examples/AnimatedGrid/hero-background",
    "meta": {
      "adoptsFrom": {
        "module": "../animated-grid",
        "name": "AnimatedGrid"
      }
    },
    "attributes": {
      "gridColumns": 6,
      "gridRows": 4,
      "animationSpeed": "slow",
      "cardOpacity": 0.25,
      "accentColor": "#00ffba"
    }
  }
}
```

**Why This Pattern?**

1. **Reusability** ‚Äî AnimatedGrid can be used in multiple sections
2. **Independent Editing** ‚Äî Grid parameters can be edited separately
3. **Composition Over Inheritance** ‚Äî Sections compose cards rather than hardcoding features
4. **Clean Separation** ‚Äî Background logic is isolated from hero content logic
5. **Testable** ‚Äî AnimatedGrid can be previewed/tested independently

