## Navigation with Section Dropdowns

### Overview

The navigation system supports **section jump menus** for pages with multiple sections. When a page has `hasDropdown: true`, the navbar displays a dropdown under that nav link showing all sections on the page with their markers (e.g., "001 ‚Äî Vision", "002 ‚Äî AI-Native Workspace").

### How It Works

1. **Layout passes sections to navbar** ‚Äî Each layout card sends its `sections` array to the navbar component
2. **Navbar filters jumpable sections** ‚Äî Only sections with `showInNav: true` appear in dropdown
3. **Dropdown renders section labels** ‚Äî Each item shows `sectionNumber` and `sectionLabel`
4. **Click scrolls to section** ‚Äî Uses anchor links or smooth scroll to section ID

### Data Flow

```
ProductLayoutCard (product page)
  ‚îú‚îÄ currentPageId: "product"
  ‚îú‚îÄ sections: [
  ‚îÇ    { sectionId: "001-hero", sectionLabel: "Vision", showInNav: true },
  ‚îÇ    { sectionId: "002-video", sectionLabel: "Demo", showInNav: true },
  ‚îÇ    { sectionId: "003-modes", sectionLabel: "AI-Native Workspace", showInNav: true },
  ‚îÇ    { sectionId: "004-stack", sectionLabel: "AI-Native Stack", showInNav: true },
  ‚îÇ    ...
  ‚îÇ  ]
  ‚îî‚îÄ Passes to navbar:
     ‚Üì
<SiteNavbar 
  @site={{@model.site}}
  @currentPageId="product"
  @sections={{@model.sections}}  ‚Üê Sections for dropdown
/>
```

