## Brand Guide Integration

**All cards in this site use the Boxel Brand Guide**, which is copied into this project and extended with logo download capabilities.

### Brand Guide Files

```
theme/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ boxel-brand-kit.gts              # Extended BrandGuide with download features
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ BrandGuide/
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ boxel-brand.json             # Brand guide instance with Boxel values
```

### Logo Access via CSS Variables

The brand guide exposes logos as CSS variables that all components can reference:

**Primary Marks** (horizontal logo):
- `--brand-primary-mark-1` ‚Äî Light background variant
- `--brand-primary-mark-2` ‚Äî Dark background variant
- `--brand-primary-mark-greyscale-1` ‚Äî Greyscale light
- `--brand-primary-mark-greyscale-2` ‚Äî Greyscale dark

**Secondary Marks** (icon only):
- `--brand-secondary-mark-1` ‚Äî Light background variant
- `--brand-secondary-mark-2` ‚Äî Dark background variant

**Social Media**:
- `--brand-social-media-profile-icon` ‚Äî Square profile icon

### Navbar Logo Usage

The Site card links to the Brand Guide, which provides logo URLs via the `markUsage` field. Access logos through the relationship:

```gts
// In components/site-navbar.gts
<template>
  <nav class="site-navbar">
    <a href="/" class="navbar-logo">
      <img 
        src={{if @isDarkMode 
          @site.brandGuide.markUsage.primaryMark2 
          @site.brandGuide.markUsage.primaryMark1
        }} 
        alt={{@site.siteTitle}}
        class="site-logo"
      />
    </a>
  </nav>

  <style scoped>
    .site-logo {
      height: var(--brand-primary-mark-min-height, 32px);
      width: auto;
    }
  </style>
</template>
```

**Note:** The CSS variable `--brand-primary-mark-min-height` is available from the brand guide's CSS output, while the actual logo URL comes from the model relationship.

